refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;

 boolis_a
 mixedobject_or_class
 stringclass
 boolallow_string&false;



 Determines if the given object_or_class is the
 class object type,
 or has class as one of its supertypes.

&reftitle.returnvalues;


 Returns &true; if object_or_class is the
 class object type,
 or has class as one of its supertypes, &false; otherwise.

  &reftitle.examples;



    is_a example


<?php
// define a class
class WidgetFactory
{
  var $oink = 'moo';
}

// create a new object
$WF = new WidgetFactory();

if (is_a($WF, 'WidgetFactory')) {
  echo "yes, \$WF is still a WidgetFactory\n";
}
?>




    Using the instanceof operator


<?php
if ($WF instanceof WidgetFactory) {
    echo 'Yes, $WF is a WidgetFactory';
}
?>
